snippet: American intelligence assessments say the group could pose a more immediate threat than the Islamic State.
abstract: American fighter jets carry out series of airstrikes in northwestern Syria that seek to kill leaders of Qaeda militant cell Khorasan, which is plotting attacks on the West.

byline.original: By BEN HUBBARD and ERIC SCHMITT
byline.contributor: Ben Hubbard reported from Baghdad, and Eric Schmitt from Washington. Mark Mazzetti contributed reporting from Washington, and Mohammed Ghannam from Beirut, Lebanon.

lead_paragraph: American intelligence assessments say the group could pose a more immediate threat than the Islamic State.
